properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 30 at 4:50AM AKST until January 30 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow and very cold wind chills to 55 below
occurring. Plan on difficult travel conditions. The cold wind
chills will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to
exposed skin. In addition, heavy drifting snow is expected.

* WHERE...In passes south of the Denali Park Entrance.

* WHEN...Until noon today.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...In passes south of the Denali Park
Entrance, north winds gusting to 30 mph are causing blowing and
drifting snow with reduced visibility and wind chills to 50
below. Motorists should be prepared for large snow drifts and
very cold wind chills.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for blowing snow means periods of
blowing snow will cause travel difficulties. The latest road
conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON AKST TODAY
